    thematic_area: '3. Effective data governance framework',
    requirement: 'An independent second‑line validation function must ensure that RDARR processes operate effectively. It should remain organisationally separate from data governance and RDARR units—or apply safeguards and segregation of duties if housed in the same function—to avoid conflicts of interest. The validation function should regularly assess RDARR capabilities across all material entities and risk types, covering all components such as IT infrastructure, data lineage, taxonomy, outsourced activities, IT changes, mergers, acquisitions, and new product launches. It must also be supported by adequate staff and strong expertise in IT, data and reporting',
    bcbs_principle_number: 1,
