    expectations: "Governance arrangements over IVU\n\n An Independent Validation Unit (IVU) is established and fulfills the following criteria:\n1. It is independent from the units involved in data governance and end to end RDARR processes. \n2. It forms an integral part of the second line of defense (2nd LoD) ensuring that the Bank's RDARR processes are functioning as intended.   \n3. It is subject to sound governance arrangements monitoring its independence with well defined roles and responsibilities.  \n\nValidation activities\n\nThe Independent Validation Unit (IVU) has established a validation framework which describes its scope of work and validation activities based on which:\n1. Regular assessments of the Institution's RDARR capabilities are performed covering all material legal entities and risk types. On the basis of the nature, size and scale of its operations the validation work with regards to material subsidiaries can either be performed at a Group or local subsidiary level ensuring compliance and consistency across the Group.\n2. The scope of work of the IVU covers all components of the end - to - end RDARR processes (e.g. IT infrastructure, data lineage and data taxonomy). \n3. Presents the annual validation plan and validation report and findings to the Board Risk Committee (BRC), for the latter to escalate significant findings to the BoD accordingly.\n4. In order to cope successfully with its responsibilities the validation It is equipped with adequate and sufficient human resources and relevant IT, data and reporting expertise.\n5. In addition the scope of work includes the oversight of outsourced functions, IT change initiatives, mergers and acquisitions and new product launches.",
